===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|ar|en}} {{m|ar|فَتْحَة||an [[opening]]}}, instance noun of the verbal noun {{m|ar|فَتْح||[[opening]]}} of the verb {{m|ar|فَتَحَ||to [[open]]}}. Refers to the mouth position when pronuncing the {{IPAchar|/a/}} vowel.

====Alternative forms====
* [[fatḥa]], [[fatHa]]

* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/fɑːthɑ/|lang=en}}

====Noun====
{{examples-right|{{lang|mul|sc=Arab|دَ}} /da/. <br> {{lang|mul|scArab|دَا}} or {{lang|mul|sc=Arab|دَى}} /dā/ [daː].}}
{{en-noun}}

# In [[Arabic]] [[script]], the [[vowel]] point for "[[a]]", appearing as a [[diagonal]] [[line]] placed above a letter and designating a short /a/: {{term|ـَ|lang=mul|sc=Arab}}. If the Arabic letters {{term|ا|lang=mul|sc=Arab}} (ʾalif) or {{term|ى|lang=mul|sc=Arab}} (ʾalif maqṣūra) immediately follow, it indicates a long /ā/.
# The vowel designated by this mark.

